{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Because the sample did not add the `Pointer Lock API` feature.\r\nLost mouse over capture when mouse hovers over canvas.\r\nWhen you go back to the canvas, the canvas thinks you are rotating the view.\r\n\r\nlook this \r\nhttps:\/\/developer.mozilla.org\/en-US\/docs\/Web\/API\/Pointer_Lock_API\r\n\r\nand this\r\nhttps:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/?q=point#misc_controls_pointerlock","created_at":"2017-11-11T02:28:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630#issuecomment-343633864","id":343633864,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MzYzMzg2NA==","updated_at":"2017-11-11T02:28:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/343633864","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/19372111?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/FishOrBear","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5MzcyMTEx","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"FishOrBear","type":"User","id":19372111,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@FishOrBear very cool, I was not aware of the Pointer Lock API. This certainly provides a way of getting around the issue, but for many use cases it may be appropriate to keep the cursor and allow the mouse to easily enter\/leave the scene.\r\n\r\nSeems like there is a moment where the transform controls stop handling the onMouseMove event and then the orbit controls start handling it and do the huge rotation.","created_at":"2017-11-13T17:39:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630#issuecomment-343997611","id":343997611,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0Mzk5NzYxMQ==","updated_at":"2017-11-13T17:41:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/343997611","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/9775178?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/brmscheiner","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3NzUxNzg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"brmscheiner","type":"User","id":9775178,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"If anyone comes across this thread in need of a hacky fix, I was able to stop this behavior by modifying the `handleMouseMoveRotate` function in `OrbitControls.js`:\r\n\r\n\tfunction handleMouseMoveRotate( event ) {\r\n\r\n\t      var currentTime = new Date().getTime();\r\n\r\n\t      var timeSinceLastRotation = currentTime - this.lastRotationTime;\r\n\t      var largeRotation =\r\n\t        Math.abs(event.clientX - rotateStart.x) > 30 || Math.abs(event.clientY - rotateStart.y) > 30;\r\n\r\n\t      if (largeRotation && timeSinceLastRotation > 750) return;\r\n\r\n\t      rotateEnd.set( event.clientX, event.clientY );\r\n\t      rotateDelta.subVectors( rotateEnd, rotateStart );\r\n\r\n\t      var element = scope.domElement === document ? scope.domElement.body : scope.domElement;\r\n\r\n\t      \/\/ rotating across whole screen goes 360 degrees around\r\n\t      rotateLeft( 2 * Math.PI * rotateDelta.x \/ element.clientWidth * scope.rotateSpeed );\r\n\r\n\t      \/\/ rotating up and down along whole screen attempts to go 360, but limited to 180\r\n\t      rotateUp( 2 * Math.PI * rotateDelta.y \/ element.clientHeight * scope.rotateSpeed );\r\n\r\n\t      rotateStart.copy( rotateEnd );\r\n\r\n\t      scope.update();\r\n\r\n\t      this.lastRotationTime = currentTime;\r\n\t}\r\n","created_at":"2017-11-13T18:58:52.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630#issuecomment-344021276","id":344021276,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDAyMTI3Ng==","updated_at":"2017-11-13T19:01:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/344021276","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/9775178?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/brmscheiner","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3NzUxNzg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"brmscheiner","type":"User","id":9775178,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/brmscheiner\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"`Pointer Lock API` This api has a headache, when I` exitPointerLock`, the mouse is still in its original position.\r\n\r\nI do not know what's the solution to this problem.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-11-14T06:41:56.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630#issuecomment-344161324","id":344161324,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12630","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDE2MTMyNA==","updated_at":"2017-11-14T06:41:56.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/344161324","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/19372111?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/FishOrBear\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/FishOrBear","subscriptions_